'''剩女'''是对[[大齡單身女性|大龄单身女性]]的贬义称呼。这个词将未婚女性比作剩饭剩菜。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Metaphorical representations of “leftover women”: between traditional patriarchy and modern egalitarianism|author=Yu, Yating|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/333661093_Metaphorical_representations_of_leftover_women_between_traditional_patriarchy_and_modern_egalitarianism|journal=Social Semiotics|issue=31|doi=10.1080/10350330.2019.1625515|year=2021|volume=2|page=248-265|access-date=2022-02-05|archive-date=2022-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220203120435/https://www.researchgate.net/publication/333661093_Metaphorical_representations_of_leftover_women_between_traditional_patriarchy_and_modern_egalitarianism}}</ref> 在[[中华全国妇女联合会|全国妇联]]的宣传下，“剩女”用来代指接近三十岁、或三十岁以上的未婚女性。<ref name="BBC">{{cite news|last=Magistad|first=Mary Kay|date=20 February 2013|title=BBC News - China's 'leftover women', unmarried at 27|work=[[BBC_News|BBC News]]|location=Beijing|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/magazine-21320560|accessdate=29 March 2013|archive-date=2013-04-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130410192314/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/magazine-21320560|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="DM">{{cite news|last=Simpson|first=Peter|date=21 February 2013|title=The 'leftover' women: China defines official age for females being left on the shelf as 27|work=[[Mail_Online|Mail Online]]|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2282249/The-leftover-women-China-defines-official-age-females-left-shelf-27.html|accessdate=29 March 2013|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111235639/https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2282249/The-leftover-women-China-defines-official-age-females-left-shelf-27.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Sebag-Montefiore|first=Clarissa|date=21 August 2012|title=Romance With Chinese Characteristics|newspaper=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|url=http://latitude.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/08/21/romance-with-chinese-characteristics/?_r=0|accessdate=2013-12-24|archive-date=2018-08-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180828203318/https://latitude.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/08/21/romance-with-chinese-characteristics/?_r=0|dead-url=no}}</ref>“剩女”一词主要在中国大陆被使用，但也在印度、北美、和亚洲其他地区被使用。<ref name="PULITZER2">{{cite news|last=Lee|first=Deborah Jian|author2=Sushima Subramanian|date=17 October 2011|title=China's Educated Women Can't Find Eligible Men|work=[[Pulitzer_Center_on_Crisis_Reporting|Pulitzer Center on Crisis Reporting]]|location=China|url=http://pulitzercenter.org/reporting/china-women-marriage-education-employment|accessdate=31 January 2019|archive-date=2016-08-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160821153340/http://pulitzercenter.org/reporting/china-women-marriage-education-employment|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="PD2">{{cite news|last=HuangJin|first=Chen Lidan|date=26 February 2013|script-title=zh:中国"剩女"现象引热议 国外网友称欲学中文来中国|work=[[People's_Daily|People's Daily]]|language=zh|trans-title=China's 'leftover women' phenomenon arouses heated debate in West|url=http://www.zj.xinhuanet.com/newscenter/sociology/2013-02/23/c_114777483.htm|accessdate=23 April 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130602215159/http://www.zj.xinhuanet.com/newscenter/sociology/2013-02/23/c_114777483.htm|archive-date=2013-06-02|url-status=dead|dead-url=no}} – [http://english.peopledaily.com.cn/90882/8144310.html English] {{Wayback|url=http://english.peopledaily.com.cn/90882/8144310.html |date=20130529022719 }}</ref> “剩女”，是那些大龄女青年得到的一个新称号，她们被称作“单身派”。日本人则称之为“被男人扔掉的女人”，也可以称为“3S女人”：Single（单身）、Seventies（大多数生于1970年代）、Stuck（被卡住了）。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://jx.ifeng.com/info/qg/detail_2015_08/18/4244418_0.shtml|title=为优质剩女正名：我们从来不愁嫁！|date=2015-08-18|access-date=2021-01-05|language=中文|archive-date=2015-09-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150913063928/http://jx.ifeng.com/info/qg/detail_2015_08/18/4244418_0.shtml}}</ref>网络上一度流行着这样的说法，25岁至28岁的未婚女性称为“初级剩女”或是“剩斗士”；28至32岁的未婚女性被称为“中级剩女”或“必剩客”；32至35岁的未婚女性则被划归“高级剩女”的行列；35岁以上还未嫁的女性则被尊称为“齐天大剩”，大龄单身女性们被贴上了种种年龄标签，而有关“剩女”的形象并不止于此，在这一方面，新闻媒体起到了推波助澜的作用，媒体的曝光不断构建起社会公众对“剩女”的形象认知。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ycwb.com/attach/201504bps.pdf|title=她，为什么“剩下”？——2016 中国城市“剩女”问题大数据研究报告|access-date=2021-01-05|language=中文}}</ref>

2007年，中国教育部发布的《中国语言生活状况报告（2006）》中，首次官方使用“剩女”一词，用以代指“已经过了社会一般所认为的[[适婚年龄|适婚年龄]]，但是仍然未结婚的女性”。<ref>{{Cite web|title=百度百科-剩女 （网络用语）|url=https://baike.baidu.com/item/%E5%89%A9%E5%A5%B3/7352570|accessdate=2020-05-30|author=|date=|format=|publisher=|language=中文|archive-date=2020-03-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305043617/https://baike.baidu.com/item/%E5%89%A9%E5%A5%B3/7352570|dead-url=no}}</ref>此后，主流媒体广泛使用“剩女”一词；“剩女”在电视、杂志、报纸、书籍中被广泛讨论，讨论聚焦于“剩女”一词的贬义含义和积极的重新定义。<ref name="UCDM">{{cite news|last1=Ng|first1=Valerie|last2=Nilsson|first2=Erik|date=12 February 2012|title=Much ado about shengnu|newspaper=[[The_China_Daily|The China Daily]]|url=http://usa.chinadaily.com.cn/epaper/2014-02/12/content_17279212.htm|accessdate=2014-04-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416220058/http://usa.chinadaily.com.cn/epaper/2014-02/12/content_17279212.htm|archive-date=2014-04-16|url-status=dead|dead-url=no}}</ref> 在2007年左右，支持中国政府的媒体早期支持使用“剩女”一词；但两年后，政府报纸对该词汇的使用进行了批评。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/magazine-21320560|title=The over-27s China calls 'leftover women'|last=Magistad|first=Mary Kay|date=2013-02-21|access-date=2019-10-02|language=en-GB|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112004022/https://www.bbc.com/news/magazine-21320560|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="chinadaily.com.cn">{{Cite web|title=Why women choose to stay out of wedlock|url=https://www.chinadaily.com.cn/opinion/2009-09/18/content_8707224.htm|website=www.chinadaily.com.cn|access-date=2019-10-02|archive-date=2020-07-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200710103817/https://www.chinadaily.com.cn/opinion/2009-09/18/content_8707224.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>

"剩女"的平行词汇为“[[光棍|光棍]]”或“剩男”，用以代指未婚男性，因为男性不结婚便无法为家族谱系增加“树枝”，后来词义扩大，泛指一切男女单身人士。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/simp/chinese_news/2011/11/111111_china_singles_day|title=中国“光棍节”性别失衡引关注|access-date=2021-01-21|language=中文|archive-date=2021-01-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210128162633/https://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/simp/chinese_news/2011/11/111111_china_singles_day}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Asian demography: The flight from marriage|date=20 August 2011|work=[[The_Economist|The Economist]]|location=Seoul and Taipei|url=http://www.economist.com/node/21526329|accessdate=18 April 2013|archive-date=2018-03-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180317200749/https://www.economist.com/node/21526329|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="TNYT2">{{cite news|last=Schott|first=Ben|date=15 March 2010|title=Leftover Ladies & 3S Women|work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|url=http://schott.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/03/15/leftover-ladies-3s-women/|accessdate=29 March 2013|archive-date=2020-11-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201118162814/https://schott.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/03/15/leftover-ladies-3s-women/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2010-04/24/content_9770152.htm|title=The Dating game by Jiangsu TV|newspaper=[[China_Daily|China Daily]]|date=2010-04-24|author=Lin Qi|accessdate=2017-07-10|archive-date=2020-03-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311024337/https://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2010-04/24/content_9770152.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lintellettualedissidente.it/filosofia/amore-appuntamenti-cina/|title=Amore con appuntamento: delirio occidentale a Chinatown|newspaper=L'Intellettuale Dissidente|author=di Francesco Pietrobelli|date=20 June 2017|language=it|accessdate=2017-07-10|archive-date=2018-08-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180828170415/http://www.lintellettualedissidente.it/filosofia/amore-appuntamenti-cina/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Marriage Squeeze, Never-Married Proportion, and Mean Age at First Marriage in China|last=Jiang|first=Quanbao|last2=Feldman|first2=Marcus W.|date=2014|journal=Population Research and Policy Review|issue=2|doi=10.1007/s11113-013-9283-8|volume=33|pages=189–204|issn=0167-5923|jstor=43671595|pmc=3948615|pmid=24634556|last3=Li|first3=Shuzhuo}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Constructing the myth of protest masculinity in Chinese English language news media: a critical discourse analysis of the representation of ‘leftover men’|author=|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/353305090_Constructing_the_myth_of_protest_masculinity_in_Chinese_English_language_news_media_a_critical_discourse_analysis_of_the_representation_of_'leftover_men'|last=Yu|first=Yating|last2=Nartey|first2=Mark|date=2021-07-13|journal=Gender and Language|issue=2|doi=10.1558/genl.18823|volume=15|issn=1747-633X|access-date=2022-06-06|archive-date=2022-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220203125042/https://www.researchgate.net/publication/353305090_Constructing_the_myth_of_protest_masculinity_in_Chinese_English_language_news_media_a_critical_discourse_analysis_of_the_representation_of_%27leftover_men%27}}</ref>

== 背景 ==

在中国，[[早婚|早婚]]、男性受到[[婚姻挤压|婚姻挤压]]是一种历史悠久的现象。在当代中国的人口统计中，[[适婚年龄|适婚年龄]]女性进入婚姻的比例实际高于男性。至2000年前左右，只有2%的30至34岁的女性未婚。相比之下，10%的同龄男性未婚。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Between Tradition and Modernity: “Leftover” Women in Shanghai|url=http://dx.doi.org/10.1111/jomf.12220|last=Ji|first=Yingchun|date=2015-07-29|journal=Journal of Marriage and Family|issue=5|doi=10.1111/jomf.12220|volume=77|pages=1057–1073|issn=0022-2445}}</ref>中国的[[计划生育政策|计划生育政策]]，以及以性别选择为目的的流产，使得中国的性别比例失调愈演愈烈。<ref name="BBC" /><ref name="DM" />自1979年计划生育政策推行以来，出生的男性比女性多出约2千万，大约每100名女婴对应120名男婴。到2020年，中国男性人口预计会比女性多出2400万。<ref>{{Cite web|title=China’s Bachelors: When Men Outnumber Women|url=https://pulitzercenter.org/projects/china-population-women-bachelor-marriage|accessdate=30 May 2020|author=Pulitzer Center on Crisis Reporting|date=17 October 2011|format=|publisher=|language=|archive-date=2020-10-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201025084653/https://pulitzercenter.org/projects/china-population-women-bachelor-marriage|dead-url=no}}</ref>全球范围内的平均数据是每103名男性对应107名女性。<ref name=REU>{{cite news |title=In China, signs that one-child policy may be coming to an end |last=Wee |first=Sui-Lee |last2=Li |first2=Hui |date=21 January 2013 |work=[[Reuters|Reuters]] |location=[[Jiuquan|Jiuquan]], China |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2013/01/21/us-china-population-idUSBRE90K0UV20130121 |accessdate=29 March 2013 |archive-date=2015-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924173419/http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/01/21/us-china-population-idUSBRE90K0UV20130121 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

据[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]报道，[[中华人民共和国国务院|中华人民共和国国务院]]于2007年推行了一项关于计划生育政策的规章，为了解决紧要的性别比例失调现象，并称其为“对社会稳定的威胁”。<ref name="NYT">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/10/12/opinion/global/chinas-leftover-women.html?_r=0|title=OP-ED CONTRIBUTOR; China's 'Leftover' Women|last=Fincher|first=Leta Hong|date=12 October 2012|work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|accessdate=29 March 2013|archive-date=2017-02-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170222150406/http://www.nytimes.com/2012/10/12/opinion/global/chinas-leftover-women.html?_r=0|dead-url=no}}</ref> 国务院还将“提升人口素质”定为其主要目标之一，并任命于1949年为“保障妇女权益”而成立的[[中华全国妇女联合会|中华全国妇女联合会]]来监督并解决这一问题。<ref name="NYT" />

对于“剩女”一词的来源暂时没有定论，但是可靠来源显示它大约于2006年进入主流使用中。<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=7YJKCAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=%22sheng+nu%22+coined#v=onepage&q=origins%20term&f=false|last=To|first=Sandy|title=China's Leftover Women: Late Marriage among Professional Women and its Consequences|date=2015|publisher=Routledge|isbn=9781317934189}}</ref> 据[[中国日报|中国日报]]2011年报道，[[柯夢波丹|时尚杂志]]中国版的主编徐巍创造了这个词。中国日报还称，这个词最初先在[[上海|上海]]被广泛使用，然后才在全国范围内流行开来。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://usa.chinadaily.com.cn/life/2011-03/13/content_12166529.htm|title=A woman's way|last=Tian|first=Gan|date=13 March 2011|work=[[China_Daily|China Daily]]|accessdate=7 April 2013|archive-date=2018-08-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180828203200/http://usa.chinadaily.com.cn/life/2011-03/13/content_12166529.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref> 2007年，[[中华人民共和国教育部|中华人民共和国教育部]]发表了一份官方声明，定义“剩女”一词为“年龄超过27周岁的未婚女性”，并将此词编入[[新华词典|新华词典]]。<ref name="NYT" /> 在随后的另一声明中，教育部进一步定义此词为因“对婚姻伴侣要求过高”而“找不到丈夫”的女性。<ref name=TDM2>{{cite news |last1=Simpson |first1=Peter |last2=De Lacey |first2=Martha |date=28 February 2013 |title='Chinese men want wives who are easier to control': How China's high-flying single women are rejected because male suitors are intimidated by their successes |work=[[Mail_Online|Mail Online]] |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-2285865/Chinese-men-want-wives-easier-control-How-Chinas-high-flying-single-women-rejected-male-suitors-intimidated-successes.html |accessdate=29 March 2013 |archive-date=2020-11-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108171722/https://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-2285865/Chinese-men-want-wives-easier-control-How-Chinas-high-flying-single-women-rejected-male-suitors-intimidated-successes.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> 据多方来源称，政府曾要求全国妇联出版多篇文章来污名化二十五至三十岁之间的未婚女性。<ref name="BBC" /><ref name="NYT" /><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.iol.co.za/business/business-news/china-stigmatises-educated-single-women-as-leftovers-1.1476068#.UWEoUKt26Fc|title=China stigmatises educated single women as 'leftovers'|date=25 February 2013|work=[[The_Independent|The Independent]]|accessdate=7 April 2013|archive-date=2020-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303233244/https://www.iol.co.za/business/business-news/china-stigmatises-educated-single-women-as-leftovers-1.1476068#.UWEoUKt26Fc|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2011年3月，在[[国际妇女节|国际妇女节]]后不久，全国妇联发表了一篇题为《剩女不值得同情》的文章。<ref name="NYT" /> 文中写道：“长相靓丽的女孩子不需要太高的学历照样可以嫁入豪门，但长相普通和丑的女孩子则很难，所以，这样的女孩子就希望能够通过提高学历来增强自己的竞争力。悲哀的是，她们不知道女人是越老越不值钱，等到自己拿到硕士、博士毕业证的时候，不料自己已经人老珠黄。” <ref name="BBC" /> 全国妇联的网站上曾有至少15篇含”剩女“一词的文章，其中包括相亲建议，但它们现在都已被移除。<ref name="BBC" />

根据2016年由羊城晚报智慧信息研究中心、华南理工大学数据新闻研究中心和中山大学心理学系联合开展的《2016 中国城市“剩女”问题大数据研究报告》显示：剩女群体中大学本科和硕士的比例较高，平均月收入2000元以下的比例居多，2000-5000元的比例其次。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=她，为什么“剩下”？ ——2016 中国城市“剩女”问题大数据研究报告|url=http://www.ycwb.com/attach/201504bps.pdf}}</ref>

== 反“剩女”污名化 ==

=== 媒体参与“剩女”去污名化 ===
“剩女”们展开了去污名化、并积极调用互联网与媒体资源，开展了骄傲使用“剩女”一词的运动。日本护肤品牌[[SK-II|SK-II]]开展了名为#changedestiny （#改变命运）的全球行动，从而赋权被“剩女”偏见影响的女性。<ref>{{Cite web|title=A Skin Care Brand Bravely Stood Up for China's 'Leftover' Women Unmarried After 25 – Adweek|url=https://www.adweek.com/creativity/skincare-brand-bravely-stood-chinas-leftover-women-unmarried-after-25-170708/|language=en-US|website=www.adweek.com|access-date=2019-01-27|archive-date=2020-06-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200609125754/https://www.adweek.com/creativity/skincare-brand-bravely-stood-chinas-leftover-women-unmarried-after-25-170708/|dead-url=no}}</ref> SK-II的全球行动影片《她最后去了相亲角》（又名《不为结婚而结婚，你的人生属于你自己》）<ref>{{Cite web|title=SK-II：「不為結婚而結婚，妳的人生屬於妳自己」|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ttQo_Aavitk|accessdate=2020-05-30|author=|date=|format=|publisher=|language=}}</ref>讲述了几名中国女性27岁后因未婚而面对的挑战。<ref name="Market Takeover">{{Citation|last=SK-II|title=SK-II: Marriage Market Takeover (Please turn on subtitle)|date=2016-04-06|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=irfd74z52Cw&t=28s|access-date=2018-11-29|archive-date=2020-11-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201110024605/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=irfd74z52Cw|dead-url=no}}</ref> 在采访中，采访对象讲到她们被父母逼婚，邀请父母来相亲角、看到她们的单人照，并回应：单身也可以活得很精彩。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.sk-ii.com/luxury-skin-care-tips/marriage-market-takeover.html|title=We're single, but not 'leftovers'|access-date=2018-11-29|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181129100841/https://www.sk-ii.com/luxury-skin-care-tips/marriage-market-takeover.html|archive-date=2018-11-29|dead-url=yes}}</ref>“相亲角”是中国父母为子女征婚的场所，父母常常携带子女的数据，用来为他们打广告，包括身高、体重、薪水、教育程度、性格等等。<ref name="Market Takeover" />

2020年，美国[[公共广播电视公司|PBS电视台]]拍摄了《剩女》(Leftover Women)纪录片。<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=Leftover Women {{!}} Independent Lens {{!}} PBS|url=https://www.pbs.org/independentlens/films/leftover-women/|accessdate=2020-05-30|work=Independent Lens|language=en-US|archive-date=2020-11-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201113060322/https://www.pbs.org/independentlens/films/leftover-women/|dead-url=no}}</ref>《剩女》由以色列籍的Shosh Shlam和Hilla Medalia导演，围绕三名中国女性（邱华梅、徐敏、蔡琪）展开。<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title=外国导演跟拍3名中国“剩女”，揭开上亿女性的辛酸：不结婚就是没人要？_邱华梅|url=http://www.sohu.com/a/393366532_616577|accessdate=2020-05-30|work=www.sohu.com|language=en}}</ref>据评论分析，该纪录片展示了跨文化视野、和对“剩女”议题的理解，体现了“剩女”们“只是选择了另一种幸福方式”、“不愿被主流的‘幸福模板’所捆绑。”<ref name=":1" />

还值得注意的是，中国英文新闻媒体更多地挑战“剩女”迷思，而不是延续它。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Metaphorical representations of “leftover women”: between traditional patriarchy and modern egalitarianism|author=Yu, Yating|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/333661093_Metaphorical_representations_of_leftover_women_between_traditional_patriarchy_and_modern_egalitarianism|journal=Social Semiotics|issue=31|doi=10.1080/10350330.2019.1625515|year=2019|volume=2|page=248-265|access-date=2022-02-05|archive-date=2022-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220203120435/https://www.researchgate.net/publication/333661093_Metaphorical_representations_of_leftover_women_between_traditional_patriarchy_and_modern_egalitarianism}}</ref>  剩女的媒体报道表现出四种截然不同的意识形态，即年龄歧视、异性恋、父权制和平等主义。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Media representations of'leftover women'in China: a corpus-assisted critical discourse analysis|author=Yu, Yating|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/336649472_Media_representations_of_'leftover_women'_in_China_a_corpus-assisted_critical_discourse_analysis|journal=Gender & Language|issue=13|doi=10.1558/genl.36223|year=2019|volume=3|page=1747–6321|access-date=2022-06-06|archive-date=2022-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220203121838/https://www.researchgate.net/publication/336649472_Media_representations_of_%27leftover_women%27_in_China_a_corpus-assisted_critical_discourse_analysis}}</ref>

=== 社会反响 ===

当今中国社会的很多权威人士都曾公开表达他们对正在发展的女权运动的不满。浙江大学社会学系教授冯钢曾在社交媒体上发表“历史证明学术界不是女生的地盘”等言论。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sixthtone.com/news/1001047/sociologist-refuses-to-apologize-for-sexist-social-media-posts|title=Sociologist Refuses to Apologize for Sexist Social Media Posts|last=Tone|first=Sixth|date=2017-10-24|work=Sixth Tone|access-date=2019-01-27|language=en|archive-date=2020-06-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200613152429/http://www.sixthtone.com/news/1001047/sociologist-refuses-to-apologize-for-sexist-social-media-posts|dead-url=no}}</ref> 多益网络是中国最大的网络游戏公司之一，其CEO徐波（徐宥箴）也曾称“一个女人，若一生生孩子不足两个，那么无论她如何努力，都注定是不幸福的。” <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hrw.org/news/2017/11/05/china-needs-stop-growing-gender-gap|title=China Needs to Stop the Growing Gender Gap|date=2017-11-05|work=Human Rights Watch|access-date=2018-11-27|language=en|archive-date=2020-09-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200922045959/https://www.hrw.org/news/2017/11/05/china-needs-stop-growing-gender-gap|dead-url=no}}</ref> 这些言论都只是大众对中国女权运动发展的声讨的冰山一角。

中国政府也站在崛起的女权运动的对立面。2015年的国际妇女节前夕，几位女权活动家因宣传反对公交性骚扰而被警方拘留。五位女性也因散发女权贴纸被公安机关拘留。此事后来被成为[[女权五姐妹|女权五姐妹]]事件。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hrw.org/news/2017/03/07/international-womens-day-china-muffles-womens-voices|title=On International Women's Day, China Muffles Women's Voices|date=2017-03-07|work=Human Rights Watch|access-date=2018-11-27|language=en|archive-date=2020-10-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201027175716/https://www.hrw.org/news/2017/03/07/international-womens-day-china-muffles-womens-voices|dead-url=no}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2017/mar/08/feminist-stickers-china-backash-women-activists|title=I went to jail for handing out feminist stickers in China {{!}} Li Maizi|last=Maizi|first=Li|date=2017-03-08|website=the Guardian|language=en|access-date=2019-01-27|archive-date=2019-09-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190918011602/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2017/mar/08/feminist-stickers-china-backash-women-activists|dead-url=no}}</ref> 2017年，当时最具网络影响力的女权自媒体[[女权之声|女权之声]]被封号，具体原因不明。

[[蔡英文|蔡英文]]是[[中华民国|中华民国]]的第一位女性总统，也是一位63岁的“剩女”。她也曾因未婚而被批评。中国官方媒体[[新华社|新华社]]曾称她“从人性的角度分析，作为单身女政客，她没有爱的情感拖累，没有‘家’的掣肘，没有子女的牵挂，在政治上的行事风格与行事策略，往往偏向情感化、个性化、极端化发展，政治权术上则在战略方向上考量少，战术细节上考量多，短期目标所示到极致，长期目标则较少顾及。” <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/taiwan-tsai-ingwen-single-shamed_us_5745bd50e4b0dacf7ad38663|title=China Shames Taiwan's New Female President For Being Single|last=Ma|first=Alexandra|date=2016-05-25|work=Huffington Post|access-date=2019-01-27|language=en-US|archive-date=2019-02-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190205163443/https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/taiwan-tsai-ingwen-single-shamed_us_5745bd50e4b0dacf7ad38663|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在这样的环境下，中国女性自发形成了很多相互支持、共同抵抗婚育压力的社交团体。一篇[[大西洋_(雜誌)|大西洋杂志]]的文章称这些社交团体的参与者超过千人。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2011/10/for-chinas-educated-single-ladies-finding-love-is-often-a-struggle/246892/|title=For China's Educated Single Ladies, Finding Love Is Often a Struggle|last=Lee|first=Sushma Subramanian, Deborah Jian|date=2011-10-19|work=The Atlantic|access-date=2019-01-27|language=en-US|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112023303/https://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2011/10/for-chinas-educated-single-ladies-finding-love-is-often-a-struggle/246892/|dead-url=no}}</ref>  Sandra Bao（白朵朵）是一家时尚杂志的创办者和编辑，她在上海创立的“剩态度”组织旨在支持未婚职业女性。她说，“父母给我们压力，媒体给我们贴标签，以及一群婚姻中介商大力呼吁单身是大问题，甚至有罪。” <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.richmond.com/news/national-world/china-s-leftover-women-face-pressure-to-marry/article_f9b17a50-a78c-5c15-a1d3-d98c3d5613fc.html|title=China's 'leftover women' face pressure to marry|last=Times|first=Los Angeles|work=Richmond Times-Dispatch|access-date=2018-11-29|language=en|archive-date=2020-06-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200613155420/https://www.richmond.com/news/national-world/china-s-leftover-women-face-pressure-to-marry/article_f9b17a50-a78c-5c15-a1d3-d98c3d5613fc.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

